post_text:
Guidelines and Criteria for Attending Bosqueville ISD Graduation Ceremony:

1. Each graduate is allowed to have ten (10) attendees.

2. Attendees must be with the Graduate at their assigned time in order to be allowed into the Stadium.

3. Each attendee must present a COVID-19 screening form at the Graduation ceremony. These forms will be issued to each Graduate for distribution prior to the ceremony.

4. Any person arriving on their own without a screening form and not with a Graduate will be turned away and not be allowed to enter the stadium.

Class of 2020! We know that the end-of-year activities and graduation are more than just a ceremony and a last farewell. They are family celebrations, community celebrations and your celebration for 12 years of hard work. While typical events make look different this year, you are no less special.

This class of 39 members is resilient, creative, bold, dedicated, smart, talented, athletic, caring and giving. We love you Class of 2020 and we are proud of you! #2020strong #bulldogpride
We will he honoring two seniors a day - stay tuned in to see all the wonderful accomplishments and activities of our 2020 Senior class.

post_text:
As most of you know Governor Abbott issued an Executive Order today. Included in that order was the closing of all schools in Texas through April 3rd.

Bosqueville ISD will continue the “work at home” delivery method of instruction for all students that was started on Wednesday, March 18th. We will continue to communicate with parents, staff and students through e-mail, our phone messaging system, our website and our District and Campus Facebook pages.

We will also continue to offer lunches during this time for our students who qualify through the free/reduced lunch program.
Due to the fact that we will have very limited staff working in the District we ask that you communicate through e-mail.

Contact information:
James.skeeler@bosquevilleisd.org
Kelly.bray@bosquevilleisd.org
Cliff.heath@bosquevilleisd.org
Brian.vasek@bosquevilleisd.org
Rachel.carter@bosquevilleisd.org

shared_text:
Bosqueville Elementary
August 26, 2015 at 5:26 PM ·

Friday will be our first pep rally! The theme will be tie dye. The pep rally will start at 2:50 and we will begin to load buses to go to the HS at 2:35. If you are picking your child up to take them to the pep rally you can pick them up at 2:35. If your child rides the bus to the pep rally then they must ride the bus back to school for dismissal. The football game is home this week. Elementary students must be accompanied by an adult. Please remind your children to stay off the track and do not play under the bleachers. The volleyball games are also at home and will start at 5:00. Come on out and support our Lady Bulldogs and Bulldogs!

Bosqueville Elementary
May 26, 2015 at 1:47 PM ·

Friday is INNOVATION DAY! Your child (1st-5th) grade will be coming home with a sheet with their project and what they will need to bring on Friday. Please look over it and make sure these items can be brought by Friday. If not, your child may need to pick another project. We will have some supplies here for the students to use. If you have any cardboard laying around at home we would love to take it off your hands. We are also looking for volunteers to come on Friday to help with projects. If you can come and help on Friday please email me at brayke@bosqueville.k12.tx.us or you can call at 752-6006. We have a ton of projects ranging from building robots to decorating cakes.

The Bulldog golf team competed at Iredell's golf tournament today in Glen Rose.

Bosqueville team one won the tournament shooting a combined 354 with Kaleb Gordon leading the way with an 85. Kaleb won third for overall score. Team one also consisted of Grahm Gonzalez, Chris Dodd, and Bryce Campbell.

Bosqueville two won third with Britt Kerr, Kenton Hill, Kade Kosar, and Joseph Weynand.

The boys did a great job.

post_text:
Bosqueville ISD hosted a Veterans’ Day Assembly at the high school gymnasium. The ceremony was student organized and led. Bosqueville FFA, NHS, and FCCLA groups were all part of the planning and implementation of the well put together event.
Mr. Bruce Mazzare, Vietnam veteran and CEO of Management Development Systems of Waco was the keynote speaker. He reminded those assembled of why Veterans’ Day was begun and also of its true meaning. Mr. Mazzare ended his speech with a challenge to those assembled to not be the generation that let the freedom that so many have fought for slip away.
Bosqueville ISD would like to convey our heartfelt gratitude to those that have or are serving in the armed forces abroad and here at home.
FFA President, Alex Smith, quoting JFK's second inaugural address.
"And so, my fellow Americans: ask not what your country can do for you--ask what you can do for your country. "

post_text:
October is Breast Cancer Awareness month and Bosqueville ISD's PINK OUT campaign month. Each year we honor some very special folks at our Pink Out pep rally and we need your help. We are looking for staff and community members that have stood up to Breast Cancer that we can honor at our Oct. 17th pep rally.
If you are fighting/have fought breast cancer, we want to honor you. If you know someone who has fought or is fighting breast cancer and would like us to honor them, let us know!

Contact Lisa Moncus at moncusli@bosqueville.k12.tx.us with their name and contact information so we may invite them.

Guests will need to be at the pep rally by 2:30 pm Friday, Oct. 17. The pep rally is held in the high school gym and is open to the public.

post_text: On October 24th, the Bosqueville Bulldogs will take on the Valley Mills Eagles. Our Bulldogs will show their spirit and get the community pumped with our Annual Homecoming Parade beginning at 2 pm that afternoon. We need your support! We are looking for volunteers to pull parade floats. If you have a truck/trailer and are interested in being a part of this spirit-filled tradition, please let us know! You can contact your child’s teacher or Mrs. Plank at 752-4878.

The Bosqueville Cheerleaders are working on the football program for the 2014.2015 Bulldog season. We would like to offer you the opportunity to place an ad in the program.

Ad prices for the 2014 football Program are as follows, please mark below.

___Back Outside Cover $200.00 (spoken for)
___Front Inside Cover $160.00
___Back Inside Cover $140.00
___Full Page $130.00
___1/2 Page $80.00
___1/4 Page $50.00

Bosqueville Elementary
August 12, 2014 at 4:45 PM ·

In order to complete registration you must bring a current (July or August) water, electric or gas bill and valid Texas state ID. If you have not brought this information to the campus your child will not be registered and placed in a class for the 2014-2015 school year. The last day to turn in registration will be Friday, August15th. If you miss this deadline you will need to wait until the first day of classes, August 25th, to complete this requirement. The office will be closed August 18th-22nd for teacher/staff development. Please make every effort to get here with this information by the end of the week. We are here 7:30-4:00. If you have questions please contact Mrs. Lisa Gjelsten at 254-752-6006. Thank you to everyone who has completed the registration process in a timely manner. It is very much appreciated.
